Format: verse
Commentary:
  - Body: An incessant "progress", never ending in contentment, means the
      condemnation of all men to a state of irremediable poverty.
    Source: Coomaraswamy; Am I My Brother's Keeper?, pp. 2-3
---
Could you from all the world all wealth procure,
More would remain, whose lack would leave you poor!
